* ============================================================
* MCC_SUPER_REGRESSIVE_SHAKEDOWN_CANARIES.DTS
*
* Purpose:
* - Aggressively regression-test the known fragile spots.
* - Label known/observed irregularities as CANARIES.
*
* House rules baked in:
* - Any CALC comparisons (= <> <= >= < >) must be wrapped:
*     CALC (<expr>)
* - Hyphenated dates must be quoted for CTOD:
*     CTOD("2000-01-01")
* - TUP is table-buffer aware for display; LIST/SMARTLIST/browsers show real DBF data.
* - Quotes required for values with spaces; optional otherwise.
* - Cursor/area/record can move due to commands; we probe RECNO before/after.
*
* ASCII ONLY: do not use smart quotes or em-dashes.
* ============================================================

SET ECHO ON
ECHO ===== SUPER REGRESSIVE SHAKE-DOWN START =====
COLOR DEFAULT

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SETUP: OPEN ALL DBF TABLES =====
SCHEMAS CLOSE
SCHEMAS OPEN DBF
SCHEMAS

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CALC: BASELINE ARITH / PRECEDENCE (should pass) =====
CALC 1
CALC 1 + 2
CALC 10 - 3
CALC 6 * 7
CALC 8 / 2
CALC (1 + 2) * 3
CALC 1 + 2 * 3
CALC 7 / 2
CALC 7.0 / 2
CALC 0 - 5
CALC -5 + 2
CALC 1 + -2
CALC (0 - 2) * 3

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CALC: COMPARISON RULE CHECK (must be parenthesized) =====
ECHO [NOTE] If any of these mis-route to CALCWRITE, the parser rule regressed.
CALC (1 = 1)
CALC (1 < 2)
CALC (2 > 1)
CALC (2 >= 2)
CALC (2 <= 2)
CALC NOT (1 = 2)
CALC ((1 = 1) AND (2 = 2))
CALC ((1 = 1) OR (1 = 2))
CALC (1 + 2 * 3 = 7)
CALC ((1 + 2) * 3 = 9)

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CALC: RHS-EXPRESSION CANARIES (known fragile) =====
ECHO [CANARY] RHS expression in equality; should be .T.
CALC (3 = 1 + 2)
ECHO [CANARY] Both sides expressions; should be .T.
CALC ((1 + 2) = (6 / 2))
ECHO [CANARY] Nested expression compare; should be .T.
CALC ((1 + 2 * 3) = (1 + (2 * 3)))

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CALC: CLOCK / DATE-TIME (no DBF required) =====
CALC DATE()
CALC TODAY()
CALC TIME()
CALC NOW()
CALC DATETIME()

ECHO [SANITY] DATE vs TODAY, NOW vs DATETIME should match.
CALC (DATE() = TODAY())
CALC (NOW() = DATETIME())

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== DATE ARITHMETIC / COMPARE CANARIES (known failures) =====
ECHO [CANARY] Should be .T. If .F., date-compare/coercion is broken.
CALC ((DATE() + 2) > DATE())
ECHO [CANARY] Should be .T. If .F., date-compare/coercion is broken.
CALC ((DATE() - 2) < DATE())

* Show the raw date arithmetic outputs too
CALC DATE() + 2
CALC DATE() - 2

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CTOD PARSING CANARIES =====
ECHO [NOTE] Hyphenated dates must be quoted. Unquoted is a canary for tokenization.
ECHO [CANARY] If CTOD(2000-01-01) "works" but compares fail, tokenization is suspect.
CALC CTOD(2000-01-01)

ECHO [EXPECTED] Quoted should parse cleanly and behave consistently.
CALC CTOD("2000-01-01")
CALC CTOD("2000/01/01")
CALC CTOD(20000101)

ECHO [SANITY] Date-to-date compares (should be .T.)
CALC (CTOD("2000-01-01") = CTOD("2000/01/01"))
CALC (CTOD("2000-01-01") = CTOD(20000101))

ECHO [CANARY] Date + 1 day equality. Expected .T. If .F., date math/compare is broken.
CALC (CTOD("2000-01-01") + 1 = CTOD("2000-01-02"))
ECHO [CANARY] Date - 1 day equality. Expected .T. If .F., date math/compare is broken.
CALC (CTOD("2000-01-01") - 1 = CTOD("1999-12-31"))

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== DTOC ROUND-TRIP CANARY =====
ECHO [CANARY] DTOC output and equality should behave predictably (string compare).
CALC DTOC(CTOD("2000-01-01"))
CALC (DTOC(CTOD("2000-01-01")) = "20000101")

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== STRING BUILTINS: BASELINE + CANARIES =====
ECHO [SANITY] Basic string funcs on literals should work.
CALC (UPPER("aBc") = "ABC")
CALC (LOWER("aBc") = "abc")
CALC (PROPER("joHN") = "John")
CALC (LEFT("ABCDE", 3) = "ABC")
CALC (RIGHT("ABCDE", 2) = "DE")
CALC (ALLTRIM("  hi  ") = "hi")

ECHO [CANARY] TRIM should remove BOTH sides. If it behaves like RTRIM only, this will fail.
CALC TRIM("  hi  ")
CALC (TRIM("  hi  ") = "hi")

ECHO [SANITY] LTRIM/RTRIM are one-sided.
CALC LTRIM("  hi  ")
CALC RTRIM("  hi  ")
CALC (LTRIM("  hi  ") = "hi  ")
CALC (RTRIM("  hi  ") = "  hi")

ECHO [SANITY] LEN/SUBSTR/AT
CALC LEN("ABCDE")
CALC SUBSTR("ABCDE", 2, 3)
CALC AT("CD", "ABCDE")

ECHO [CANARY] RAT may be unimplemented (previously returned .F.)
CALC RAT("A", "BANANA")

ECHO [SANITY] REPLICATE/SPACE
CALC REPLICATE("x", 5)
CALC SPACE(3)

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== OPEN STUDENTS: ANCHOR RECORD AND PROBE CURSOR MOVES =====
SELECT STUDENTS
AREA
ECHO [STEP] Anchor on a known record by LOCATE.
LOCATE FOR LNAME = TAYLOR
ECHO [INFO] Current record snapshot:
RECNO
TUP
TUP SID
TUP LNAME
TUP FNAME
TUP DOB
TUP ENROLL_D
TUP GPA
TUP EMAIL

ECHO [PROBE] Cursor restore behavior around LIST.
ECHO [NOTE] LIST may move internally then restore. We check RECNO before/after.
ECHO [PROBE] RECNO before LIST:
RECNO
LIST 1
ECHO [PROBE] RECNO after LIST (should match before if restore works):
RECNO
ECHO [NOTE] If RECNO changed and stayed changed, cursor restore regressed or is command-specific.

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== STUDENTS: DATE FIELD ALGEBRA + CANARIES =====
ECHO [SANITY] Date arithmetic on DBF date fields should print YYYYMMDD.
CALC DOB
CALC DOB + 1
CALC DOB - 1
CALC DATEADD(DOB, 30)
CALC DATEADD(DOB, -30)

ECHO [SANITY] Day count should agree between DATEDIFF and date-date subtraction.
CALC DATEDIFF(DATE(), DOB)
CALC DATE() - DOB

ECHO [CANARY] These printed equal before but compared .F. (type/coercion mismatch).
CALC (DATEDIFF(DATE(), DOB) = (DATE() - DOB))

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== BOOLEAN/PREDICATE: FIELD-ONLY SANITY =====
ECHO [NOTE] BOOLEAN uses predicate grammar, not CALC expr grammar.
BOOLEAN GPA > 3
BOOLEAN GPA < 3
BOOLEAN GPA >= 2 AND GPA <= 4

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== LOCATE/FIND/SEEK: SMOKE + CURSOR NOTES =====
ECHO [NOTE] These commands may move the record pointer. We show RECNO before/after.
TOP
RECNO
LOCATE FOR LNAME = DAVIS
RECNO
TUP

TOP
RECNO
LOCATE FOR LNAME = TAYLOR
RECNO
TUP

TOP
RECNO
FIND LNAME = TAYLOR
ECHO [PROBE] After FIND, record pointer may be unchanged or last hit; check:
RECNO

TOP
RECNO
SEEK LNAME = DAVIS
ECHO [PROBE] After SEEK, pointer should land on found record:
RECNO
TUP

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== TABLE BUFFER DISPLAY CANARIES (TUP vs LIST) =====
ECHO [RULE] Only TUP is buffer-aware for display. LIST shows actual DBF content.

LOCATE FOR LNAME = TAYLOR
ECHO [BASELINE] Show current values (real DBF):
LIST 1
ECHO [BASELINE] Show current values (buffer-aware):
TUP

ECHO [STEP] Enable table buffering, edit a field, then compare TUP vs LIST.
TABLE ON
REPLACE FNAME WITH "DeraldNew"

ECHO [CANARY] TUP should show the buffered change immediately.
TUP

ECHO [CANARY] LIST should still show the OLD DBF value (until COMMIT) if buffering is working.
LIST 1

ECHO [PROBE] RECNO before COMMIT (should not drift unexpectedly):
RECNO
TUP SID

ECHO [STEP] COMMIT (may rebuild indexes; should preserve current record identity).
COMMIT

ECHO [CANARY] After COMMIT, record identity should still be the same student.
ECHO [CANARY] If SID/record changes unexpectedly, COMMIT record-preserve is broken.
RECNO
TUP
TUP SID

ECHO [SANITY] After COMMIT, LIST should now show the new value (real DBF updated).
LIST 1

ECHO [STEP] Restore original value to keep run reversible.
TABLE ON
REPLACE FNAME WITH "Derald"
COMMIT
LIST 1
TUP

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CLEAN SHUTDOWN =====
SCHEMAS
SCHEMAS CLOSE
ECHO ===== SUPER REGRESSIVE SHAKE-DOWN END =====
QUIT
